title: ASX to rise, Wall St stumbles, gold loses lustre
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, despite weakness on Wall Street and in oil, iron ore and gold. $A slips on rising $US. Bitcoin eyes $US60,000.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Dow edges higher
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by the Dow. Iron ore rises. Credit Suisse tumbles. $A little changed.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to open higher as JobKeeper ends
summary: Australian shares are set to rise as markets lifted before a shortened Easter week and investors looked to the end of pandemic unemployment benefits.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open higher as Nasdaq stays low
summary: Australian shares are set to open flat as tech stocks continued to slump despite forecasts of stronger growth in the US economy.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to slip as US tech stocks fall
summary: Australian shares are drop slightly after US technology stocks declined modestly, bucking a slight upward trend on sharemarkets.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open flat despite unsettled US markets
summary: Australian shares are set to open flat after choppy trading on Wall Street, while Jerome Powell and Janet Yellen told Congress the US economy was still vulnerable to the pandemic.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open slightly lower as Wall St marks anniversary of virus crash
summary: Australian shares are set to drop slightly exactly a year after the US pandemic sharemarket plunge that eventually turned into a roaring bull market.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open lower as markets drop back from a big week
summary: Australian shares are likely to drop as sharemarkets lost ground in the aftermath of a strong five days.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to drop as Wall Street turns down the heat
summary: Australian shares are expected to open lower as markets reversed moves and treasury yields hit new peaks.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX futures fluctuate as Fed leaves rates unchanged
summary: Australian shares are set for an uncertain open as bond yields fell from earlier peaks. As expected, the Federal Reserve has made no changes in its QE program.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to drop but tech stocks boost Wall Street
summary: The Australian sharemarket is set to open lower but technology shares have jumped ahead as the S&P and Nasdaq touched new highs.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to lift slightly as Wall St hits high amid focus on central banks
summary: Australian shares are set to open slightly higher as markets watch the US Federal Reserve and Europe shuts down the AstraZeneca vaccine.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to slip, Fed policy meeting in focus
summary: Australian shares are poised to edge lower as global investors take in another spike in US bond yields and await this week’s Federal Reserve decision.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, S&P 500 and Dow reset records on tech rally
summary: Both the Dow and S&P 500 reset record highs as techs powered a rally on the Nasdaq. The S&P 500 is within reach of the 4000 point mark.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, US inflation data muted
summary: The Dow closed above 32,000 for the first time after the latest consumer price report tempered concerns about inflation. US 10-year yield little changed.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Nasdaq leaps 4pc as techs rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, after Nasdaq rebounded. Tesla surged near 20pc. US bond yields eased.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise; Dow advances on rotation trade
summary: Australian shares are poised to extend their fast start to the week as the Dow leapt higher. Techs dragged the Nasdaq down, again. $A slips.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to leap after techs power Wall Street bounce
summary: Australian shares are poised to open 1.6 per cent higher, bolstered by a surge in the US paced by previously hammered technology shares.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX futures point to lower open, Wall St extends slide
summary: It was a volatile day of trading in New York with the Dow moving in a 900-point range and the US 10-year yield rising back through 1.5 per cent.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, tech slide hits S&P 500, Nasdaq
summary: Australian shares appear poised for a modest opening loss. US stocks were mostly lower amid renewed selling of the mega techs. Bitcoin tops $US51,000.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge higher, Wall St consolidates
summary: Australian shares are set to rise at the open, though gains could be checked as US stocks reset lower after the previous session’s surge. $A higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Dow up 600 points, Nasdaq surges
summary: Australian shares are to rise near 1pc at the open as techs powered Wall Street higher. Nasdaq up 3pc. RBA policy meeting on agenda. $A leaps.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to bounce, bond selloff eases
summary: Australian shares appear set to open higher, recouping some of Friday’s heavy losses, as the US Treasury market steadied. $A tumbles.
author: Timothy Moore
